### [4 Kings (2 Kings) Chapter 24](../../../bib/kjv/kg2024.htm#001.md)

[4 Kings (2 Kings)](../../../bib/kjv/kg2001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">kg2 24:0</span></span>

Overview

[Kg2 24:1](../../../bib/kjv/kg2024.htm#001.md), Jehoiakim, first subdued by
Nebuchadnezzar, then rebelling against him, procures his own ruin; [Kg2
24:5](../../../bib/kjv/kg2024.htm#005.md), Jehoiachin succeeds him; [Kg2
24:7](../../../bib/kjv/kg2024.htm#007.md), The king of Egypt is vanquished
by the king of Babylon; [Kg2 24:8](../../../bib/kjv/kg2024.htm#008.md),
Jehoiachin's evil reign; [Kg2 24:10](../../../bib/kjv/kg2024.htm#010.md),
Jerusalem is taken and carried captive into Babylon; [Kg2
24:17](../../../bib/kjv/kg2024.htm#017.md), Zedekiah is made king, and
reigns ill, unto the utter destruction of Judah.

